1000004700120@unknown@formal@none@1@S@Here, it is assumed that the probability of observing the ⌊/i⌊^th^⌋/⌋ word ⌊/w⌊,i,⌋/⌋ in the context history of the preceding ⌊/i-1/⌋ words can be approximated by the probability of observing it in the shortened context history of the preceding ⌊/n-1/⌋ words (⌊/n⌊^th^⌋ order ⌊>Markov property>⌋)./⌋@@@@1@45@@oe@26-8-2013
1000004700130@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The conditional probability can be calculated from n-gram frequency counts: ⌊× P(w_i|w_{i-(n-1)},\\ldots,w_{i-1}) = \\frac{count(w_{i-(n-1)},\\ldots,w_{i-1})}{count(w_{i-(n-1)},w_{i-1},\\ldots,w_i)}×⌋@@@@1@14@@oe@26-8-2013
