1000004700150@unknown@formal@none@1@S@⌊=Example¦3=⌋@@@@1@1@@oe@26-8-2013
1000004700160@unknown@formal@none@1@S@In a bigram (n=2) language model, the probability of the sentence ⌊/I saw the red house/⌋ is approximated as ⌊×P(I,saw,the,red,house) \\approx P(I) P(saw|I) P(the|saw) P(red|the) P(house|red)×⌋@@@@1@26@@oe@26-8-2013
