1000004800630@unknown@formal@none@1@S@It turns out that when you select the ⌊×k×⌋ largest singular values, and their corresponding singular vectors from ⌊×U×⌋ and ⌊×V×⌋, you get the rank ⌊×k×⌋ approximation to X with the smallest error (⌊>Frobenius norm>⌋).@@@@1@35@@oe@26-8-2013
